[
    {
        "content": "<p>Iterating over consecutive pairs in a <code>List</code> is a pretty common pattern. Right now, this is how I code it (you may have a better idea?):</p>\n<div class=\"codehilite\" data-code-language=\"Elm\"><pre><span></span><code><span class=\"nv\">list</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"nf\">=</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"p\">[</span><span class=\"mi\">0</span><span class=\"p\">,</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"mi\">10</span><span class=\"p\">,</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"mi\">20</span><span class=\"p\">,</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"mi\">30</span><span class=\"p\">,</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"mi\">40</span><span class=\"p\">,</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"mi\">50</span><span class=\"p\">]</span>\n<span class=\"nv\">result</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"nf\">=</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"kt\">List</span><span class=\"nf\">.</span><span class=\"nv\">map2</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"nv\">list</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"p\">(</span><span class=\"nv\">list</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"nf\">|&gt;</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"kt\">List</span><span class=\"nf\">.</span><span class=\"nv\">sublist</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"p\">{</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"nv\">start</span><span class=\"nf\">:</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"mi\">1</span><span class=\"p\">,</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"nv\">len</span><span class=\"nf\">:</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"p\">(</span><span class=\"kt\">List</span><span class=\"nf\">.</span><span class=\"nv\">len</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"nv\">list</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"nf\">-</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"mi\">1</span><span class=\"p\">)})</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"nf\">\\</span><span class=\"nv\">a</span><span class=\"p\">,</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"nv\">b</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"nf\">-&gt;</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"p\">(</span><span class=\"nv\">a</span><span class=\"p\">,</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"nv\">b</span><span class=\"p\">)</span>\n<span class=\"nv\">expect</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"nv\">result</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"nf\">==</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"p\">[(</span><span class=\"mi\">0</span><span class=\"p\">,</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"mi\">10</span><span class=\"p\">),</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"p\">(</span><span class=\"mi\">10</span><span class=\"p\">,</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"mi\">20</span><span class=\"p\">),</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"p\">(</span><span class=\"mi\">20</span><span class=\"p\">,</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"mi\">30</span><span class=\"p\">),</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"p\">(</span><span class=\"mi\">30</span><span class=\"p\">,</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"mi\">40</span><span class=\"p\">),</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"p\">(</span><span class=\"mi\">40</span><span class=\"p\">,</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"mi\">50</span><span class=\"p\">)]</span>\n</code></pre></div>\n<p>It's not trivial to come up with this, and it's pretty hard to read. Perhaps we could have a <code>List</code> function for that? For example:</p>\n<div class=\"codehilite\" data-code-language=\"Elm\"><pre><span></span><code><span class=\"nv\">list</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"nf\">=</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"p\">[</span><span class=\"mi\">0</span><span class=\"p\">,</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"mi\">10</span><span class=\"p\">,</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"mi\">20</span><span class=\"p\">,</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"mi\">30</span><span class=\"p\">,</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"mi\">40</span><span class=\"p\">,</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"mi\">50</span><span class=\"p\">]</span>\n<span class=\"nv\">result</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"nf\">=</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"nv\">list</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"nf\">|&gt;</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"kt\">List</span><span class=\"nf\">.</span><span class=\"nv\">slidingWindows</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"p\">{</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"nv\">size</span><span class=\"nf\">:</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"mi\">2</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"p\">}</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"nf\">\\</span><span class=\"nv\">window</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"nf\">-&gt;</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"nv\">window</span>\n<span class=\"nv\">expect</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"nv\">result</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"nf\">==</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"p\">[[</span><span class=\"mi\">0</span><span class=\"p\">,</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"mi\">10</span><span class=\"p\">],</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"p\">[</span><span class=\"mi\">10</span><span class=\"p\">,</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"mi\">20</span><span class=\"p\">],</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"p\">[</span><span class=\"mi\">20</span><span class=\"p\">,</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"mi\">30</span><span class=\"p\">],</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"p\">[</span><span class=\"mi\">30</span><span class=\"p\">,</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"mi\">40</span><span class=\"p\">],</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"p\">[</span><span class=\"mi\">40</span><span class=\"p\">,</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"mi\">50</span><span class=\"p\">]]</span>\n</code></pre></div>\n<p>We could also provide a few more optional arguments:</p>\n<div class=\"codehilite\" data-code-language=\"Elm\"><pre><span></span><code><span class=\"nv\">list</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"nf\">=</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"p\">[</span><span class=\"mi\">0</span><span class=\"p\">,</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"mi\">10</span><span class=\"p\">,</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"mi\">20</span><span class=\"p\">,</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"mi\">30</span><span class=\"p\">,</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"mi\">40</span><span class=\"p\">,</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"mi\">50</span><span class=\"p\">,</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"mi\">60</span><span class=\"p\">,</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"mi\">70</span><span class=\"p\">,</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"mi\">80</span><span class=\"p\">,</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"mi\">90</span><span class=\"p\">]</span>\n<span class=\"nv\">result</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"nf\">=</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"nv\">list</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"nf\">|&gt;</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"kt\">List</span><span class=\"nf\">.</span><span class=\"nv\">slidingWindows</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"p\">{</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"nv\">size</span><span class=\"nf\">:</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"mi\">3</span><span class=\"p\">,</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"nv\">start</span><span class=\"nf\">:</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"kt\">At</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"mi\">1</span><span class=\"p\">,</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"nv\">end</span><span class=\"nf\">:</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"kt\">Before</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"mi\">9</span><span class=\"p\">,</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"nv\">step</span><span class=\"nf\">:</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"mi\">2</span><span class=\"p\">,</span><span class=\"w\">  </span><span class=\"nv\">keepRemainder</span><span class=\"nf\">:</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"kt\">Bool</span><span class=\"nf\">.</span><span class=\"nv\">true</span><span class=\"p\">}</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"nf\">\\</span><span class=\"nv\">window</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"nf\">-&gt;</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"nv\">window</span>\n<span class=\"nv\">expect</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"nv\">result</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"nf\">==</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"p\">[[</span><span class=\"mi\">10</span><span class=\"p\">,</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"mi\">20</span><span class=\"p\">,</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"mi\">30</span><span class=\"p\">],</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"p\">[</span><span class=\"mi\">30</span><span class=\"p\">,</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"mi\">40</span><span class=\"p\">,</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"mi\">50</span><span class=\"p\">],</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"p\">[</span><span class=\"mi\">50</span><span class=\"p\">,</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"mi\">60</span><span class=\"p\">,</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"mi\">70</span><span class=\"p\">],</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"p\">[</span><span class=\"mi\">70</span><span class=\"p\">,</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"mi\">80</span><span class=\"p\">]]</span>\n</code></pre></div>\n<p>In this example, <code>List.slidingWindows</code> acts like <code>List.map</code> but it maps over windows. Perhaps it should instead walk over the windows? We would need to add a state in this case. Or perhaps we could have both <code>List.mapSlidingWindows</code> and <code>List.walkSlidingWindows</code>.</p>\n<p>Wdyt?</p>",
