    {
        "content": "<p>I don't think it should have start or end. Leave that to sublist called before this function</p>",
        "id": 472389229,
        "sender_full_name": "Brendan Hansknecht",
        "timestamp": 1727149243
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>Also, not sure the standard on the edge slices. I feel like most common, all slices would be the exact same size and edges would be ignored... But not sure fully</p>",
        "id": 472389415,
        "sender_full_name": "Brendan Hansknecht",
        "timestamp": 1727149329
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>I think making the windows then letting the user map or walk should be mostly fine due to seamless slices.</p>",
        "id": 472389481,
        "sender_full_name": "Brendan Hansknecht",
        "timestamp": 1727149376
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>I think List.partition is a nice name for this functionality, <a href=\"https://clojuredocs.org/clojure.core/partition\">https://clojuredocs.org/clojure.core/partition</a></p>",
        "id": 472407493,
        "sender_full_name": "Nils Hjelte",
        "timestamp": 1727159294
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>We've <a href=\"#narrow/stream/231634-beginners/topic/List.2Ewalk.20with.20.22sliding.20window.22/near/451137188\">talked about this before</a>, I think we should add it.</p>",
        "id": 472425367,
        "sender_full_name": "Anton",
        "timestamp": 1727164823
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>Partition isn’t quite the same as it produces non overlapping sublists</p>",
        "id": 472478364,
        "sender_full_name": "Isaac Van Doren",
        "timestamp": 1727179825
    },
    {
        "content": "<p><span class=\"user-mention silent\" data-user-id=\"611722\">Isaac Van Doren</span> <a href=\"#narrow/stream/304641-ideas/topic/List.2EslidingWindows/near/472478364\">said</a>:</p>\n<blockquote>\n<p>Partition isn’t quite the same as it produces non overlapping sublists</p>\n</blockquote>\n<p>I would also guess that from the name alone, but in clojure it's possible to overlap if the step is smaller than the partition size</p>\n<p>another advantage is that partition is a short descriptive word that can encompass all this related functionality</p>\n<p>in my opinion clojure api is very nice, though it obviously needs adjustment for how the things are done in Roc</p>",
        "id": 472491835,
        "sender_full_name": "Artem Shamsutdinov",
        "timestamp": 1727183631
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>Personally I think window or slidingWindow is a much better name than partition. Partition has a lot of assumptions in my experience related to various possible algorithms and designs (for example partitioning for sorting).</p>\n<p>That said, at first glance, closure API seems reasonable (thought would need to pay attention to how padding works more). Also, probably a great API to return an iterator once we have them.</p>",
        "id": 472497855,
        "sender_full_name": "Brendan Hansknecht",
        "timestamp": 1727185298
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>Elixir calls this ”chunk\", and has several variants: <a href=\"https://hexdocs.pm/elixir/1.12/Enum.html#chunk_every/4\">https://hexdocs.pm/elixir/1.12/Enum.html#chunk_every/4</a></p>",
        "id": 472536503,
